    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fc689148_71930fbe",
        "filename": "ttq/internal/lessors/datastore/ds.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 187,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-20T23:18:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "construction itself is cheap.\nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/ttq/internal/partition/partition.go?q\u003d%22type%20SortedPartitionsBuilder%20struct%22\u0026ss\u003dchromium\u0026originalUrl\u003dhttps:%2F%2Fcs.chromium.org%2F\n\nThe 4 loops (one inside Exclude + one inside big.Ints comparisons) are actually not necessary cheap if number of leases \u0026 partitions grows.\nI think it\u0027s hard to reach 30 active leases with 1 minute lease expiry given sustained writes are at 1 QPS.\nIn my tests, I think i reached ~15 active leases, but due to the nature of work distribuition, the total number of partitions leased was also ~O(100).\n   Update: It\u0027s not clear whether Firestore-Datastore won\u0027t run faster since I\u0027m no longer inserting root entity every time.\n\nUnfortunately, I can\u0027t theoretically bound number of partitions to even O(active_leases^2).\nI\u0027ll follow up with an improvement here. Worst case, I\u0027ll truncate resulting slice to at most 5 partitions, which would provide for \u003c1ms computation time even with 100 active leases.",
      "parentUuid": "2711d582_62602cbf",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 187,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 187,
        "endChar": 57
      },
